title: NASA Invites Media to Next SpaceX Resupply Launch to Space Station
summary: Media accreditation is open for SpaceX’s 28th commercial resupply mission for NASA to the International Space Station. Liftoff of the SpaceX Dragon cargo spacecraft on the company’s Falcon 9 rocket is targeted no earlier than 12:34 p.m. EDT Saturday, June 3, from Launch Complex 39A at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center in Florida.

title: NASA to Discuss Science on Next SpaceX Cargo Launch to Space Station
summary: NASA will host a media teleconference at 2 p.m. EDT Tuesday, May 30, to discuss the next science investigations, technology demonstrations, crew supplies, and hardware bound for the International Space Station aboard SpaceX’s 28th commercial resupply services mission for the agency.

title: SpaceX set for launch of CRS-28 ISS resupply mission
summary: SpaceX will attempt to launch the Crew Resupply Mission 28 (CRS-28) mission to the International Space Station (ISS) on June 5 at 11:47 PM EDT (15:47 UTC) from Launch Complex 39A (LC-39A) at the Kennedy Space Center in Florida. The window for this launch is instantaneous, which put pay to Sunday’s initial attempt due to high winds in the booster recovery zone.
